<HEADLINE> White Sox Put Scott Eyre on DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP)-- The Chicago White Sox placed reliever Scott Eyre  
on the 15-day disabled list Tuesday, and recalled infielder Liu 
Rodriguez from Double-A Birmingham. 
</P>
<P>
	Eyre left in sixth inning of the second game of Chicago's  
doubleheader loss Monday against the Seattle Mariners, with pain in 
his left shoulder. White Sox trainer Herm Schneider said Eyre has 
an impingement of his rotator cuff, and the extent of the injury 
won't be known until the inflammation subsides. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodriguez, 22, was with the White Sox from June 6 to August 11,  
hitting .188 in 24 games. 
</P>
<P>
	Eyre, 27, was recalled June 20 and went 1-1 with a 7.56 ERA in  
21 games for Chicago. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
