<HEADLINE> Giants Send Stan Javier to Houston </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- The San Francisco Giants traded outfielder  
Stan Javier to the Houston Astros for pitching prospect Joe Messman 
today. 
</P>
<P>
	Javier, a 15-year major league veteran, has hit .276 with three  
home runs and 30 RBI in 112 games this season with the Giants. 
</P>
<P>
	The trade to Houston allows Javier to become a full-time player  
with a playoff-contending team, said Giants general manager Brian 
Sabean. 
</P>
<P>
	``Houston had some ongoing interest in Stan, heightened by their  
recent injury bug,'' Sabean said. 
</P>
<P>
	Messman, a 24-year-old right-hander, is 2-4 this season with 15  
saves and a 2.54 ERA in 44 relief appearances for Single-A 
Kissimmee. 
</P>
<P>
	Javier, 35, is a .266 career hitter with 48 home runs and 426  
RBI in 1,549 games. He has also played for the New York Yankees, 
Oakland Athletics, Los Angeles Dodgers, Philadelphia Phillies and 
the California Angels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
