<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> MIT Student Dies From Laughing Gas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CAMBRIDGE, Mass. (AP) -- An MIT junior was found dead in his dorm  
room early Tuesday after using a plastic bag to inhale laughing 
gas, campus officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	The body of Richard Guy, 22, was discovered shortly after  
midnight Monday. Guy, of Mission Viejo, Calif., was a physics 
major. 
</P>
<P>
	The medical examiner said Guy died from asphyxiation as a result  
of nitrous oxide intoxication. 
</P>
<P>
	Pure nitrous oxide dissolves in the bloodstream, pushing oxygen  
out from the blood into the lungs, depriving the brain and other 
organs of oxygen. Dentists frequently use it as a painkiller. 
</P>
<P>
	Massachusetts Institute of Technology officials released few  
other details and did not return phone calls seeking comment. 
</P>
<P>
	Classes aren't scheduled to begin at MIT until Sept. 7, but  
freshmen and some upperclassmen had already moved into their rooms. 
</P>
<P>
	In September 1997, 18-year-old freshman Scott Krueger died three  
days after he was found in an alcohol-induced coma on a fraternity 
floor. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
