<HEADLINE> California Gunman Remains at Large </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GARDEN GROVE, Calif. (AP) -- A gunman who killed two people and  
wounded four others when he opened fire at an auto accessories 
store remained at large today as police sought a motive. 
</P>
<P>
	The attack Monday at Robotek began when the man started firing  
in the parking lot. He then burst inside the store and continued 
shooting, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Witnesses reported that the attacker fled in a gray minivan,  
possibly with another man, Sgt. Dennis Ellsworth said. 
</P>
<P>
	One victim died in the parking lot and the other inside the  
store. Three others were in critical condition late Monday at the 
University of California, Irvine, Medical Center in Orange, 
hospital spokeswoman Kim Lachance said. 
</P>
<P>
	Another victim -- a 15-year-old boy -- was shot in the ankle and  
treated and released from a hospital, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	It was unclear whether the victims were employees, customers or  
bystanders, Sgt. Todd Elgin said. A motive for the attack remained 
unknown. Detectives didn't immediately return phone calls this 
morning seeking further detail. 
</P>
<P>
	Garden Grove is about 35 miles southeast of Los Angeles.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
