<HEADLINE> Orioles Complete Baines Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BALTIMORE (AP) -- The Baltimore Orioles on Tuesday acquired  
left-hander Jimmy Hamilton as the player to be named in the trade 
that sent Harold Baines to the Cleveland Indians. 
</P>
<P>
	Baines was traded to Cleveland last Friday. The Orioles earlier  
acquired right-hander Juan Aracena in the trade. 
</P>
<P>
	Hamilton, 24, is in his fourth professional season. He was 1-2  
with a 5.18 ERA in 24 games for Triple-A Buffalo. He was called up 
to Buffalo on June 20 after starting the season at Double-A Akron, 
where he was 0-2 with a 3.73 ERA in 25 games. 
</P>
<P>
	He has pitched exclusively in relief the last two seasons after  
spending two years as a starter. Hamilton will be assigned to the 
Orioles' Triple-A affiliate in Rochester. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
