<HEADLINE> Astros Acquire Javier From Giants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- The Houston Astros acquired outfielder Stan  
Javier from the San Francisco Giants for minor league reliever Joe 
Messman on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The 35-year-old Javier is hitting .276 with three home runs and  
30 RBIs in 112 games this season. The switch-hitter has made 45 
starts in left field, 29 in right and two in center for the Giants. 
</P>
<P>
	``Stan gives us a valuable veteran presence on our club,''  
Astros general manager Gerry Hunsicker said. ``His versatility will 
be a great asset down the stretch. He is a winning player who knows 
what it takes to win a championship.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Javier, a 15-year veteran, has played with the Giants since  
1996. He made his major league debut with the New York Yankees in 
1984. He was originally signed as a non-drafted free agent by the 
St. Louis Cardinals on in 1981. 
</P>
<P>
	Messman, a 24-year-old right-hander, was 3-4 with a 2.43 ERA in  
45 games for Class A Kissimmee this season. He ranked first on the 
club with 15 saves and struck out 47 in 59.1 innings. 
</P>
<P>
	Messman, 24, was drafted by the Astros in the sixth round of the  
1997 draft out of Oregon State. 
  	   	
</P>
