<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Police Guns Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- In a story about police plans to destroy weapons,  
The Associated Press erroneously reported on Aug. 29 that the 
Chicago Police Department has sold guns on the secondhand market. 
</P>
<P>
	Chicago police spokesman Patrick Camden said the department  
destroys guns it no longer needs. 
  	   	
</P>
