<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Tuesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Office Depot, down 1/16 at 10 7/16  
</P>
<P>
 *Staples, down 3/16 at 21 3/4 on the Nasdaq 
</P>
<P>
	Shares of most office supply stores fell after Office Depot said  
late Monday it will miss earnings expectations for the rest of 
1999. Office Depot cited weaker sales of basic office supplies, 
commercial sales and price erosion on paper supplies. 

</P>
<P>
 *Cadence Design Systems Inc., up 1 1/2 at 13 5/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Banc Boston Robertson Stephens upgraded its rating on shares of  
Cadence after the company unveiled its new printed circuit board 
systems unit. The unit was formed through Cadence's $121 million 
acquisition of OrCad Inc. 

</P>
<P>
 *Dun &AMP; Bradstreet Corp., up 2 9/16 at 26 3/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Harris Associates L.P., a major institutional shareholder, has  
urged Dun &AMP; Bradstreet to hire an investment bank to solicit 
takeover offers. Harris estimated that an acquiring company may be 
willing to pay twice the current stock price for the information 
services company. 

</P>
<P>
 *Mastech Corp., down 5/16 at 27 15/16    	
</P>
<P>
	GE Capital, a unit of General Electric Co., will invest $30  
million in Mastech, an information technology services provider. 
The companies will also form a joint venture to sell business 
processing services. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Fatbrain.com Inc., up 9 1/16 at 24 1/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Fatbrain.com will allow authors to publish and sell their work  
on its Internet site, with Fatbrain.com keeping a portion of the 
profits. The company expects the service to be particularly 
attractive for publishers of 75-page to 100-page nonfiction books. 

</P>
<P>
 *Focal Inc., up 1 5/8 at 5 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	The U.S. Food and Drug Administration will allow Focal to  
initiate a clinical trial for its FocalSeal-S surgical sealant 
product. The product is designed to prevent fluid leaks following 
neurosurgical procedures. 

</P>
<P>
 *Amylin Pharmaceuticals Inc., up 1 13/32 at 3 29/32    	
</P>
<P>
	Amylin said its diabetes drug candidate, Symlin, was successful  
in lowering primary glucose levels in a one-year study of diabetes 
patients who use insulin. The company has not yet submitted 
applications for regulatory review. 




  	   	
