<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Treasury Bond Prices Little Changed / Bonds  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Treasury bond prices were little changed at  
midday. 
</P>
<P>
	The price of the Treasury's main 30-year bond was down 1-32  
point, or 31 1/4 cents per $1,000 in face value, around midday, while 
its yield hovered around the 6.05 percent level of late Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Yields on three-month Treasury bills were 4.96 percent as the  
discount fell 0.05 percentage point from Monday's auction to 4.83 
percent. Six-month yields were 5.18 percent as the discount dipped 
0.01 percentage point from the weekly auction to 4.98 percent. 
One-year yields fell to 5.25 percent as the discount fell 0.03 
percentage point from late Monday to 4.98 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Yields are the interest bonds pay by maturity, while the  
discount is the interest at which they are sold. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
