<HEADLINE> Cardinals Call Up Eduardo Perez </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- The St. Louis Cardinals called up Eduardo Perez  
on Tuesday night, just in time for his father to perhaps see him 
play. 
</P>
<P>
	Tony Perez is the assistant general manager of the Florida  
Marlins, who conclude a three-game series Wednesday night in St. 
Louis. Eduardo Perez, a first baseman like his father, batted .322 
for Triple-A Memphis. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm excited to see him,'' Tony Perez said. ``He went down,  
worked hard and had a good year. The Cardinals are very excited 
about what he did.'' 
</P>
<P>
	St. Louis also recalled catcher Marcus Jensen and right-hander  
Mark Thompson from Memphis. General manager Walt Jocketty said 
there will be several more callups after Memphis' season ends Sept. 
6. 
</P>
<P>
	Perez, 29, led Memphis with 18 home runs and 82 RBIs in 118  
games, and was second on the team with 31 doubles. 
</P>
<P>
	Jensen, 26, batted .291 with eight homers and 44 RBIs in 72  
games. He also played for the U.S. team in the Pan American Games 
last month. 
</P>
<P>
	Thompson, 28, was 2-6 with a 5.13 ERA in 11 games for the  
Cincinnati Reds' Triple-A affiliate in Indianapolis before being 
released. He appeared in nine games with Memphis, eight of them 
starts, and was 4-2 with a 2.94 ERA. 
</P>
<P>
	Thompson has a 16-20 career major league record with a 6.12 ERA  
with the Colorado Rockies from 1994-98. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
