<HEADLINE> Warrant Issued for Sports Agent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GAINESVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- A judge has signed an arrest warrant  
for sports agent Sean Alfortish, who is accused of funneling money 
to former University of Florida players. 
</P>
<P>
	Chief assistant state attorney Bill Cervone said the  
Louisiana-based agent has agreed to turn himself in to authorities 
in Gainesville within the next two weeks. Alfortish will be charged 
with violating Florida's agent law. 
</P>
<P>
	The Florida Times-Union cited sources Tuesday as saying the  
state attorney had proof that Alfortish bought former Florida 
player Tim Beauchamp wheel rims valued at $1,500. The sources also 
said Alfortish is accused of paying Beauchamp and former player 
Dock Pollard up to $500 per month. 
</P>
<P>
	Alfortish's attorney, Rick Stanley, released a statement saying  
his client is innocent. Alfortish is the first agent charged in the 
10-month investigation by University Police. 
</P>
<P>
	Police officials said the investigation involving agent Tank  
Black is ongoing. 
</P>
<P>
	Illegal agent activity is punishable in the state of Florida by  
a maximum of five years in prison and a $5,000 fine. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
